Ask HN: 'Stimulant' Drugs/Meds; help needed w.a dead-end I've reached
text:
Some time ago, I was diagnosed with a number of cognitive issues, one of which is 'addressed' with a stimulant called Vyvanse.

In the 1st year or so it wasn’t a panacea, but it was undoubtedly the single-biggest help to me getting on w.life, & I was doing "all the right things" at that time, not just popping pills! At times, it was truly a godsend/revelation, to stick with the religious expressions! ;-P

However, for ~2yrs+? now, it's felt like it's not doing much, if anything, even if I go off it for long periods & then resume, it's just not the same?! Once kicked-in, I’m pretty sure it's always made me sleepy in the 1st ~2hr, but it feels like that’s #the only thing# left nowadays!

Recently, my psychiatrist said; "...It does nothing to address ‘tiredness’ (quite sure that wasn't always the case, + nothing like this was said in the early days) & more importantly, I should still feel/notice improved clarity-of-thought/concentration."

It's hard to judge that with a high degree of confidence, but I’m quite sure that was never markedly improved, if at all. I feel the bigger part I got out of it was not focus/concentration, but rather; energy/drive/will, & that’s been mostly-totally absent for ages now!

We’ve also tried Concerta a few times, but the feeling each time, was that it wasn’t quite as helpful, so we’d always go back to Vyvanse. She says they’re my only 2 options in Australia, for addressing ADHD-like & executive-function issues.

Are there other options, or great resources, that folks can point me to? Mainly interested in ideas for drugs/meds, but I’m open to other suggestions. I do address my issues with more than just drugs, but I’m dearly wanting to get that part working effectively again!

I have sought the counsel/opinion of other psychiatrists, but, they're pretty much the same.

Man, this was exhausting to type on an ipad pro 12.9 gen.2, whilst sitting on the toilet! >.>

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lisdexamfetamine | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methylphenidate

Ask HN: Play Store has killed my app by not fixing a bug of theirs
text:
I am unsure what to do, I don't usually complain publicly. So I have this app and I managed to get some users interested that want to pay! There is a bug on the subscription screen of Google play which effectively doesn't let anyone subscribe. 
I have exchanged 12 emails in 2 months! up to now with Google which basically say this: "Our technical team is working on it".
As we all know if you get users that can't pay and your product is Freemium it can die a slow death and I see people uninstalling after failing to use it. I could increase the usage limit for now I guess.
Has anybody escalated/expedited this process successfully?
